{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, in the Isle of Man, from what he told me, he, he, he was actually the postman there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they all had to find some sort of an occupation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he, he in fact, dished out the post, I think.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had, I mean, he wasn't imprisoned there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Though naturally, he was away from his wife.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But by and large, he had a very comfortable life like everybody else did.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And very soon afterwards-- and I really don't know to what extent, to what the length of time he stayed there-- he was released.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he then went back to the home where-- where he lived with his wife.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On his birthday in the air raid shelter, when I was in the air raid shelters in the evenings at night, I had very little else to do, and so I took up knitting.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I-- wool was, of course, rationed during the war, but I obtained somehow some eight ounces of gray wool.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I started knitting a scarf for him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the stitches, although the pattern said 60 stitches, it varied from 55 to 65, I very proudly sent that to my father in London.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I got a thank you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They acknowledged the parcel, but a week later I got the parcel back from my mother which contained two pairs of gray socks.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she said, your father unfortunately doesn't like wearing a scarf, and so [LAUGHS] I've undone the scarf, and I've made some socks out of it for you.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My parents were bombed out three or four times by doodlebugs and various other devices.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they lived in the underground, South, South Wimbledon Underground Station for about three months.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
